<span class="pagesubheading">What is Counselling?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
<p>Counselling is a method of identifying practical solution to an identified problem. Counselling can help you to understand your problem more deeply and deal with more efficiently. One should take counselling form as open, respective and confidential forum.</p>
<span class="pagesubheading">Who is the Counsellor?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
<p>A counsellor is a helping professional, offers support and understands, listen and respond to your problems.</p>
<span class="pagesubheading">What kind of problems should be discussed with the counsellor?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
<ul>
<li>Academics problems</li>
<li>Peer pressure</li>
<li>Emotional stress</li>
<li>Relationship crisis</li>
<li>Career oriented decisions </li>
<li>Drugs or Alcohol addiction</li>
<li>Home sickness &amp; Loneliness</li>
<li>Sleep disorders</li>
<li>Anxiety</li>
<li>Time management</li>
<li>Low self-confidence</li>
<li>Any other problem can also be discussed</li>
</ul>
<span class="pagesubheading">How SCC maintains the Confidentiality?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
<p>Privacy maintained strictly by the centre in all the cases. The information shared and records maintained are kept safe and confidential. We protect the confidentiality and release personal data only according to prescribed laws or institute policies. So, no need to worry about the leakage of data.</p>
<span class="pagesubheading">How effective is Counselling?</span>
<img src="<?php echo $root?>images/h2.png" width="100%" />
<p>Counselling is effective when the recipient is willing and agrees to seek help.</p>
